textDelta: Why does electricitiy travel faster through muscle? The electric current through muscle is faster because muscles are more dense than other types of tissue.

what is the redistribution-with-growth policy? The redistribution-with-growth policy is a policy that would redistribute wealth in order to increase the number of people who have access to education, health care, and other basic needs.

what are the elements of the redistribution-with-growth policy? The elements of the redistribution-with-growth policy are: -Redistribution of wealth from the rich to the poor -Redistribution of wealth from the middle class to the poor -Redistribution of wealth from the middle class to the rich -Redistribution of wealth from the rich to the poor and the rich -Targeting of public spending to achieve redistribution
what food commodities are rising? Some food commodities are rising faster than others. Cereal, milk, and meat are all increasing in price.
what food commodities are rising with urbanization? Some food commodities that are rising with urbanization are meat, milk, vegetables, fruits, grains, and seafood.
